arch:property.oc:show_val: A small to medium unit of fill that looks a lot like the rest of the 65xx series. The unit is about 1/2 03 long bone fragments but ribs and vertebra are well represented. There are the epiphyseal end splinters from both upper and lower limb bones and some teeth and feet. The foot bones, especialy the phalanges are highly fragmented into many pieces of less than 1 cm. This suggests the material was well worked over by dogs, despite the fairly low level of digestion. Perhaps the lack of digestion is due to rapid burial ? Or the dog poo was moved off site? Burning is 5-10% but most of what is burnt is carbonized, including some larger pieces. The rest of the asemblage is relatively unweathered bone. Abrasion and trampling are rare, and most of the small pieces are at least 1cm and identifiable to long bone fragment. Three bird bones including a possible goose bone were exported for further study. A number of microfauna bones, includng an almost complete skeleton were pulled for further study. Flot Smpl. 2 (4436) >4mm, diagnostics only The flot sample corresponds to the description of the dry sieved material. All the diagnostics are caprids, including one fragment of very young skull. Fish and Microfauna bones were pulled and bagged separately for future study. Last Number = 114
